intro: Calytrix duplistipulata, commonly known as the two-stipule calytrix, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Myrtaceae, which includes eucalyptus and other aromatic plants. The plant is characterized by its small, white or pink flowers that are clustered in inflorescences. Its leaves are typically narrow and lance-shaped, with a rough texture. Calytrix duplistipulata is often found in coastal and sandy soils, thriving in well-drained environments.
